            </div>
            <div style="margin-top:8px;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:6px;">
              <span class="epic-btn success">✓ Accept</span>
              <span style="font-size:11px;color:var(--text-sm);">— saves the bed day entry</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- STEP 8 — Finalize Link -->
        <div class="flow-step">
          <div class="step-connector"><div class="step-dot green">8</div><div class="step-line last"></div></div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <div class="step-phase">Finalize Account Link</div>
            <div class="step-title">Select Auth/Cert → Assign → Verify Hosp Acct</div>
            <div class="step-desc">Return to the <strong>Auth/Cert List</strong>. Click once to highlight the REF283 entry. Click <span class="epic-btn success">✓ Assign</span>. The <strong>Hosp Acct</strong> column will populate with a number — confirming the authorization is linked to the admission account and ready for billing.</div>
            <div class="fields" style="margin-top:8px;">
              <span class="field green">Hosp Acct: [Account #] populated ← confirms active link</span>
            </div>
            <div class="callout ok" style="margin-top:8px;">
              <div class="callout-label">✓ Outcome — Workflow 3 Complete</div>
              REF283 submitted. Authorization linked to the residential admission. Bed days documented. Account ready for billing. Initial authorization setup is fully complete.
            </div>
