        </div>

        <div style="border:1px solid var(--teal);border-radius:8px;padding:10px 12px;background:var(--teal-lt);">
          <div style="font-size:9.5px;font-weight:700;color:var(--teal);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.5px;margin-bottom:4px;">📊 BARC-10</div>
          <div style="font-size:11.5px;color:#134E4A;line-height:1.5;">Brief Assessment of Recovery Capital — 10-item standardized screening tool. Listed third under SUS Assessments. Complete as indicated by program protocol.</div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <!-- CalOMS callout -->
      <div style="margin-top:10px;border:1px solid var(--teal);border-radius:8px;padding:10px 14px;background:var(--teal-lt);">
        <div style="font-size:9.5px;font-weight:700;color:var(--teal);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.5px;margin-bottom:4px;">📋 CalOMS — State Reporting (separate sidebar group)</div>
        <div style="display:flex;gap:16px;flex-wrap:wrap;font-size:11.5px;color:#134E4A;line-height:1.5;">
          <div><strong>Admission</strong> — Required at episode start. Demographic + substance use baseline data for DHCS reporting.</div>
          <div><strong>Annual Update</strong> — Required each year the client remains enrolled.</div>
          <div><strong>Discharge</strong> — Required at episode end. Treatment outcome + discharge destination.</div>
          <div><strong>Admin Discharge</strong> — Administrative closure record.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Status indicators -->
      <div class="section-divider" style="margin-top:18px;"><hr><span>Assessment Completion Status</span><hr></div>
      <div class="three-col">
        <div style="background:var(--green-lt);border:1px solid var(--green);border-radius:8px;padding:10px 13px;">
          <div style="font-size:10px;font-weight:700;color:var(--green);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.5px;margin-bottom:3px;">✅ Complete</div>
          <div style="font-size:11.5px;color:#14532D;line-height:1.5;">All fields filled. Marked Complete and closed. Visible to BHS UM for authorization review.</div>
        </div>
        <div style="background:var(--amber-lt);border:1px solid var(--amber);border-radius:8px;padding:10px 13px;">
          <div style="font-size:10px;font-weight:700;color:#92400E;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.5px;margin-bottom:3px;">⏳ In Progress</div>
          <div style="font-size:11.5px;color:#78350F;line-height:1.5;">Partial data entered, not yet marked Complete. UM cannot view. Cannot submit auth.</div>
        </div>
        <div style="background:var(--coral-lt);border:1px solid var(--coral);border-radius:8px;padding:10px 13px;">
          <div style="font-size:10px;font-weight:700;color:var(--coral);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.5px;margin-bottom:3px;">🔴 Not Started</div>
          <div style="font-size:11.5px;color:#7F1D1D;line-height:1.5;">Flowsheet never opened. Blocks all downstream authorization steps.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>


<!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<!-- WORKFLOW 6 — Reauthorization                               -->
<!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<div id="w6" class="page">
  <div class="guide-card">
    <div class="guide-header">
      <div class="guide-num">6</div>
      <div class="guide-header-text">
        <h2>Residential Reauthorization — Continued Stay</h2>
        <div class="purpose">Justify ongoing residential placement at each authorization period · Submit via BHS UM Work Queue</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="guide-body">

      <div class="two-col" style="margin-bottom:16px;">
        <div class="mini-card">
          <h4>📅 Select Request Level</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>1st continued stay request (30-day)</li>
            <li>2nd continued stay request (60-day)</li>
            <li>3rd continued stay request (90-day)</li>
            <li>4th or Other — specify</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="mini-card">
          <h4>🏥 Current ASAM LOC</h4>
          <ul>
            <li><span class="field teal" style="font-size:10px;">3.1</span> Clinically Managed Low Intensity</li>
            <li><span class="field amber" style="font-size:10px;">3.3</span> Clinically Managed Population-Specific</li>
            <li><span class="field coral" style="font-size:10px;">3.5</span> Clinically Managed High Intensity</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="section-divider"><hr><span>For Each Checked Dimension — Complete All Four Items</span><hr></div>

      <table class="dim-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th style="width:28px;">#</th>
            <th style="width:170px;">Dimension</th>
            <th style="width:90px;">Severity (0–4)</th>
            <th>30-Day Progress / Challenges</th>
            <th>Clinical Rationale for Continued Stay</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><span class="dim-num">I</span></td>
            <td><strong>Acute Intoxication / Withdrawal</strong></td>
            <td><span class="field amber" style="font-size:9.5px;">0=None · 4=Severe</span></td>
            <td style="font-size:11px;color:var(--text-sm);">Withdrawal sx changes, MAT response, lab trends</td>
            <td style="font-size:11px;color:var(--text-sm);">Ongoing withdrawal risk needing 24-hr monitoring?</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><span class="dim-num">II</span></td>
            <td><strong>Biomedical Conditions</strong></td>
            <td><span class="field amber" style="font-size:9.5px;">0=None · 4=Severe</span></td>
            <td style="font-size:11px;color:var(--text-sm);">Medical stability, wound care, chronic conditions</td>
            <td style="font-size:11px;color:var(--text-sm);">Unstabilized medical needs requiring residential?</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><span class="dim-num">III</span></td>
            <td><strong>Emotional / Behavioral / Cognitive</strong></td>
            <td><span class="field amber" style="font-size:9.5px;">0=None · 4=Severe</span></td>
            <td style="font-size:11px;color:var(--text-sm);">Psychiatric stability, affect regulation, trauma</td>
            <td style="font-size:11px;color:var(--text-sm);">Co-occurring MH destabilizing recovery?</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><span class="dim-num">IV</span></td>
            <td><strong>Readiness to Change</strong></td>
            <td><span class="field amber" style="font-size:9.5px;">0=None · 4=Severe</span></td>
            <td style="font-size:11px;color:var(--text-sm);">Motivation, stage of change, engagement</td>
            <td style="font-size:11px;color:var(--text-sm);">Ambivalence needing intensive motivational work?</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><span class="dim-num">V</span></td>
            <td><strong>Relapse / Continued Use Potential</strong></td>
            <td><span class="field amber" style="font-size:9.5px;">0=None · 4=Severe</span></td>
            <td style="font-size:11px;color:var(--text-sm);">Coping skills, triggers, cravings</td>
            <td style="font-size:11px;color:var(--text-sm);">High relapse risk without 24-hr structure?</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><span class="dim-num">VI</span></td>
            <td><strong>Recovery / Living Environment</strong></td>
            <td><span class="field amber" style="font-size:9.5px;">0=None · 4=Severe</span></td>
            <td style="font-size:11px;color:var(--text-sm);">Housing stability, sober network, social support</td>
            <td style="font-size:11px;color:var(--text-sm);">Unsafe environment requiring residential placement?</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <div class="section-divider" style="margin-top:18px;"><hr><span>Summary &amp; Plan — Required for Every Reauth</span><hr></div>
      <div class="callout stop" style="margin-bottom:12px;">
        <div class="callout-label">🛑 UM Will Not Approve Without Both</div>
        Every reauthorization must include both a clinical summary and a detailed discharge plan. Vague or missing discharge plans are the #1 reason UM returns requests.
      </div>
      <div class="two-col">
        <div style="border:1px solid var(--teal);border-radius:8px;padding:12px;background:var(--teal-lt);">
          <div style="font-size:10px;font-weight:700;color:var(--teal);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.5px;margin-bottom:5px;">Clinical Summary</div>
          <div style="font-size:11.5px;color:#134E4A;line-height:1.6;">Brief narrative of clinical rationale supporting continued residential stay at time of the request.</div>
        </div>
        <div style="border:1px solid var(--amber);border-radius:8px;padding:12px;background:var(--amber-lt);">
          <div style="font-size:10px;font-weight:700;color:#92400E;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.5px;margin-bottom:5px;">Detailed Discharge Plan</div>
          <ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;font-size:11.5px;color:#78350F;line-height:1.65;">
            <li>▸ Next level of care identified</li>
            <li>▸ Referrals made (with dates)</li>
            <li>▸ Follow-up appointments confirmed</li>
            <li>▸ Warm handoffs documented</li>
            <li>▸ Supports for safe transition</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>


<!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<!-- WORKFLOW 7 — Discharge Workflow                            -->
<!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<div id="w7" class="page">
  <div class="guide-card">
    <div class="guide-header">
      <div class="guide-num">7</div>
      <div class="guide-header-text">
        <h2>Resident Discharge Workflow — Six-Stage Sequence</h2>
        <div class="purpose">Follow in order — each stage has a dependency on the previous · Hard Discharge is irreversible</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="guide-body">

      <div class="phase-strip">
        <div class="phase-item ph1" style="font-size:9px;">1. Pre-Discharge</div>
        <div class="phase-item ph2" style="font-size:9px;">2. Transition</div>
        <div class="phase-item ph3" style="font-size:9px;">3. Documentation</div>
        <div class="phase-item ph4" style="font-size:9px;">4. State Reporting</div>
        <div class="phase-item ph5" style="font-size:9px;">5. Op. Closure</div>
        <div class="phase-item ph6" style="font-size:9px;">6. Hard Discharge</div>
      </div>

      <div class="flow">

        <div class="flow-step">
          <div class="step-connector"><div class="step-dot" style="background:#1B2A4A;">1</div><div class="step-line"></div></div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <div class="step-phase">Stage 1 — Pre-Discharge</div>
            <div class="step-title">Verify Daily Notes &amp; Care Plan Are Signed</div>
            <div class="step-desc">Review the clinical chart. All daily progress notes must be signed and the current Care Plan co-signed before initiating discharge.</div>
            <div class="callout stop"><div class="callout-label">🛑 Hard Stop</div>Unsigned notes or Care Plan block Hard Discharge. Resolve all signatures first.</div>
            <div class="fields" style="margin-top:6px;">
              <span class="field coral">All Daily Notes — Signed ✓</span>
              <span class="field coral">Care Plan — Co-Signed ✓</span>
              <span class="field coral">Outstanding Orders — Resolved ✓</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flow-step">
          <div class="step-connector"><div class="step-dot" style="background:#1E6B8A;">2</div><div class="step-line"></div></div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <div class="step-phase">Stage 2 — Transition Planning</div>
            <div class="step-title">Document Warm Handoffs &amp; Follow-Up Appointments</div>
            <div class="step-desc">Confirm and document all post-discharge arrangements. Each handoff should be documented as a communication in the chart.</div>
            <div class="two-col" style="margin-top:8px;">
              <div class="mini-card"><h4>🤝 Warm Handoffs</h4><ul><li>Receiving program contacted</li><li>Client introduced to next provider</li><li>Records transfer authorized (42 CFR)</li></ul></div>
              <div class="mini-card"><h4>📅 Appointments</h4><ul><li>OP SUD program intake date</li><li>PCP / MAT prescriber follow-up</li><li>MH continuation appointment</li></ul></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flow-step">
          <div class="step-connector"><div class="step-dot teal">3</div><div class="step-line"></div></div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <div class="step-phase">Stage 3 — Documentation</div>
            <div class="step-title">New Note: BHS SUS Discharge</div>
            <div class="step-desc">Navigate to <strong>Assessment Docs</strong> → <span class="epic-btn primary" style="font-size:10px;">+ New Note</span>. Select note type <span class="field amber" style="font-size:10px;">BHS SUS Discharge</span>.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flow-step">
          <div class="step-connector"><div class="step-dot green">4</div><div class="step-line"></div></div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <div class="step-phase">Stage 4 — State Reporting</div>
            <div class="step-title">Complete CalOMS Discharge Flowsheet</div>
            <div class="step-desc">Navigate to <strong>SUS Assessments Tab</strong> → <strong>CalOMS Discharge</strong> flowsheet. Complete all required DHCS fields.</div>
            <div class="callout stop"><div class="callout-label">🛑 DHCS Mandate</div>Cannot be back-filled after Hard Discharge. Missing data risks contract non-compliance.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flow-step">
          <div class="step-connector"><div class="step-dot amber">5</div><div class="step-line"></div></div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <div class="step-phase">Stage 5 — Operational Closure</div>
            <div class="step-title">Return Belongings &amp; Close MAR</div>
            <div class="step-desc">Complete all operational tasks before Hard Discharge.</div>
            <div class="fields" style="margin-top:5px;">
              <span class="field gray">Belongings returned — signed receipt</span>
              <span class="field coral">MAR — Closed &amp; medications reconciled</span>
              <span class="field gray">Room/Bed — marked Available</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flow-step">
          <div class="step-connector"><div class="step-dot coral">6</div><div class="step-line last"></div></div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <div class="step-phase">Stage 6 — Administrative Hard Discharge</div>
            <div class="step-title">Hard Discharge — Closes the Admission Encounter</div>
            <div class="step-desc">The final irreversible step. Closes the residential encounter, removes from census, locks clinical documentation, and triggers billing finalization.</div>
            <div class="callout stop"><div class="callout-label">⚠ Irreversible</div>Cannot be undone without IT/admin intervention. Confirm all five prior stages are complete before clicking.</div>
            <div class="callout ok" style="margin-top:8px;"><div class="callout-label">✓ Outcome</div>Patient removed from census. Encounter closed. Bed available. Discharge paperwork available via Media Manager.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>


<!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<!-- WORKFLOW 8 — Discharge Plan vs. Discharge Summary          -->
<!-- ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<div id="w8" class="page">
  <div class="guide-card">
    <div class="guide-header">
      <div class="guide-num">8</div>
      <div class="guide-header-text">
        <h2>Discharge Plan vs. Discharge Summary</h2>
        <div class="purpose">Two separate documents — different purposes, audiences, and timing</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="guide-body">

      <div class="callout info" style="margin-bottom:16px;">
        <div class="callout-label">💡 Key Distinction</div>
        Confusing these two documents leads to incomplete authorizations and regulatory deficiencies. Both may be required for a complete discharge.
      </div>

      <div class="two-col">
        <div class="compare-card plan">
          <div class="compare-header">📋 Discharge Plan — Option A<div style="font-size:10px;font-weight:400;opacity:.85;margin-top:1px;">Forward-looking · Aftercare-focused · Required for Reauth</div></div>
          <div class="compare-body">
            <div class="compare-row"><div class="compare-label">Perspective</div><div class="compare-val"><strong>Forward-looking.</strong> Describes what happens after the client leaves.</div></div>
            <div class="compare-row"><div class="compare-label">Primary Use</div><div class="compare-val">Required for every <strong>Reauthorization</strong>. UM will not approve without it.</div></div>
            <div class="compare-row"><div class="compare-label">Core Content</div><div class="compare-val"><ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;font-size:11.5px;line-height:1.7;"><li>▸ Next level of care identified</li><li>▸ Step-down program/facility named</li><li>▸ Medication plan at discharge</li><li>▸ Referrals made with dates</li><li>▸ Follow-up appointments confirmed</li><li>▸ Housing / transportation plan</li></ul></div></div>
            <div class="compare-row"><div class="compare-label">Timing</div><div class="compare-val">Updated at <em>each auth period</em> and finalized at discharge</div></div>
            <div class="compare-row"><div class="compare-label">Epic Location</div><div class="compare-val"><span class="field teal">Reauth Order — Discharge Plan Section</span></div></div>
            <div class="callout stop" style="margin-top:4px;"><div class="callout-label">🛑 Reauth Requirement</div>Missing or vague Discharge Plan = #1 reason UM returns reauth requests.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="compare-card summary">
          <div class="compare-header">📄 Discharge Summary — Option B<div style="font-size:10px;font-weight:400;opacity:.8;margin-top:1px;">Retrospective · Comprehensive · Clinical record</div></div>
          <div class="compare-body">
            <div class="compare-row"><div class="compare-label">Perspective</div><div class="compare-val"><strong>Retrospective.</strong> Reviews the full residential stay from admit to discharge.</div></div>
            <div class="compare-row"><div class="compare-label">Primary Use</div><div class="compare-val">Clinical record, continuity of care. Not used for auth decisions.</div></div>
            <div class="compare-row"><div class="compare-label">Core Content</div><div class="compare-val"><ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;font-size:11.5px;line-height:1.7;"><li>▸ Presenting problem at admission</li><li>▸ Treatment milestones achieved</li><li>▸ Progress across ASAM dimensions</li><li>▸ Medications during stay</li><li>▸ Incidents / behavioral events</li><li>▸ Reason for exit (planned/AMA)</li></ul></div></div>
            <div class="compare-row"><div class="compare-label">Timing</div><div class="compare-val">Completed <em>at discharge only</em></div></div>
            <div class="compare-row"><div class="compare-label">Epic Location</div><div class="compare-val"><span class="field amber">Assessment Docs → BHS SUS Discharge Note</span></div></div>
            <div class="callout warn" style="margin-top:4px;"><div class="callout-label">⚠ Not a Substitute</div>Discharge Summary does NOT replace the Discharge Plan for reauthorization.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="section-divider" style="margin-top:20px;"><hr><span>Quick Decision Table</span><hr></div>
      <table class="dim-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Situation</th><th>Discharge Plan?</th><th>Discharge Summary?</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Submitting a reauthorization to UM</td><td style="color:var(--green);font-weight:600;">✅ Required</td><td style="color:var(--mid);">❌ Not used for auth</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Client leaving the program today</td><td style="color:var(--green);font-weight:600;">✅ Finalize</td><td style="color:var(--green);font-weight:600;">✅ Complete</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Sending records to a new treatment program</td><td style="color:var(--amber);font-weight:600;">⚠ Include (aftercare plan)</td><td style="color:var(--green);font-weight:600;">✅ Primary document</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Quality review / audit request</td><td style="color:var(--mid);">Optional</td><td style="color:var(--green);font-weight:600;">✅ Yes</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <div class="footnote"><strong>42 CFR Part 2:</strong> Discharge Summaries containing SUD treatment information require a valid, signed ROI before release to any external party. Standard HIPAA TPO exceptions do not apply to 42 CFR Part 2 records.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>


<script>
function show(id, btn) {
  document.querySelectorAll('.page').forEach(p => p.classList.remove('active'));
  document.querySelectorAll('.tab-btn').forEach(b => b.classList.remove('active'));
  document.getElementById(id).classList.add('active');
  btn.classList.add('active');
  window.scrollTo({ top: 0, behavior: 'smooth' });
}
</script>
